0, this class will have a hard time doing so.\r\n\r\nFor example, if I want the PID to issue commands between [-1, 0], these checks will fail to truncate max command if it goes above 0.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/2943bf3e08f46ced48b46a0ec6726f2967a92942/gazebo/common/PID.cc?at=default&amp;fileviewer=file-view-default#PID.cc-154\" rel=\"nofollow\">PID check against cmdMin and cmdMax</a> is hardcoded around a zero command. In general, if one wishes to limit PID commands between a range not closed around 0, this class will have a hard time doing so.</p>\n<p>For example, if I want the PID to issue commands between [-1, 0], these checks will fail to truncate max command if it goes above 0.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2016-06-28T19:55:16.405222+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:20:40.750603+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 1997}